The game class:
When the game class conductor is run it should create a list that contains 16 square objects

Every square in the 4 x 4 grid will have values associated with it:
A method that creates a square that appears in a random box that is empty, with a random number either 2 or 4
A method for each direction that the user chooses to move in
A method that creates the game as a giant print statement basically.

There will need to be a square class that is used in the game class:

Square class contains:
Variables:
int value
boolean empty
A method to give a value
A method to remove a value
A method to get the value
A method to get the boolean empty

Main class:
Check constantly for input

